<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12175e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12175e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12175e"> 175(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Fintan teaches I history / to SP</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In mediaeval times two theories obtained as to the preservation of the history of the early inhabitants of the isle, one of these was, that Fintann from time to time appeared visibly among the Gael, and taught history to the bards and others. Thus he is represented as coming up from his favourite haunts in the mountains of Kerry, and <mark>relating the history of Ireland to St. Patrick</mark>. <small> Standish O'Grady, <a name="OGSE" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OGSE"><cite title="source">Selected Essays and Passages</cite></a> (1918) 56-7</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
